node.text:
Did a little seasonal twist on my favorite kale salad! Made with apples, almonds, parmesan, garlic, and lemon. I made this dish at the beautiful @flamingo_estate!!

A little side note: They called me Chef Carina, which is super sweet, but I don't typically call myself a chef, since I don't have chef experience or training! Always need to throw that out there, because I'm a home cook and a food blogger and really admire chefs who've put in proper time in the kitchen. 

#kale #kalesalad

Banana Split Overnight Oats!! 🍌

Dropping the recipe today on my newsletter, good mood food! Subscribe at the link in my bio to get the recipe delivered straight to your inbox! Or stay tuned for the link in bio in just a few hours

node.text:
A California Greek Salad — like kinda, but not fully 😂 This was a clean out the fridge situation inspired by some Greek flavors — and also California produce! 

Chickpeas, chopped tomatoes, chopped red onion, chopped kale & romaine, feta, lemon, olive oil, red wine vinegar, and some salt, pepper, aleppo pepper, and a lot of dried oregano

No recipe here because I made it on a whim, but it doesn’t really need one! Put as much of each as your heart desires and taste test — just don’t forget to massage your kale!!

node.text:
Peach Lemonade Slushy, because it’s peach season, baby!! I made this beverage as part of the #PrimaPeachChallenge (details on the challenge & recipe for the drink below!). This drink tastes amazing with booze or as a virgin drink, so take your pick! What’s most important is its star ingredient, peaches!! 

I used @PrimaWawona peaches in this recipe — they are fresh, juicy, and tasty, just as a perfect peach should be. If you’re a peach fan, you should join the #PrimaPeachChallenge. All you have to do is share your creative, picturesque content of the ways you’re enjoying Prima® Peaches all summer long, and you’ll have chance to win some cash. For more info, go to https://prima.com/primapeachchallenge

PEACH LEMONADE SLUSHY RECIPE (serves 4)
3 peaches, cut into slices
1 cup lemon juice (about 5 large lemons)
2-3 tbsp honey (2 for a tangier drink, 3 for sweeter)
5 cups ice
Optional: Alcohol of choice (I suggest gin or vodka, but whiskey could work too! Use 1.5 shots per serving, you can blend in or mix later if some people don’t want it spiked)

Add everything to a blender, and blend until smooth! Garnish with a fresh peach slice

#ad

node.text:
Scallion Yogurt Potato Salad with Chili Crunch!! Potatoes are bae, and I want to eat them in every form!! Recipe below

For this recipe, I was lightly inspired by a recipe I saw from @mollybaz — I loved the idea of a scallion filled potato salad especially with some creamy Greek yogurt and some spicy spicy! 

RECIPE (serves 4-6)
2 lbs baby gold potatoes
1 1/4 tsp salt, divided
1 1/2 cups full fat Greek yogurt
4 large scallions, thinly sliced at a diagonal
2 cloves garlic, crushed or thinly chopped
1-2 tsp chile crunch/chile crisp/chile oil (1 tsp for less spicy, 2 for more spicy)
Drizzle of sesame oil

Add potatoes and 1 tsp salt to a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil, and then simmer for 15-20 minutes until potatoes can be pierced with a fork. Drain and then immediately add to a bowl of ice water to cool. Once potatoes have cooked, peel, and then chop. Add to a large bowl.

In a medium bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, 1/4 tsp salt, sliced scallions (leaving a handful to sprinkle on top) and the chopped/crushed garlic. Mix together, and then add to the bowl with potatoes and toss.

Add to a bowl and top with the chili crisp and remaining scallions!

node.text:
This is the easiest egg salad ever: Mashed Soft Boiled Eggs with tomatoes, olive oil, salt, black and red pepper, and oregano over a piece of toast drizzle with olive oil and rubbed with garlic. Plus a little fresh dill and basil because herbs make everything better. 

I used 4 eggs for 2 people and probably about 1/2 cup tomatoes. Just drizzle on some good quality evoo and add a pinch of the other stuff. I soft boiled the eggs for about 7 min — check my story highlights for how I do perfect soft boiled eggs every time!

node.text:
I made these Spicy Mayo Shrimp Tacos from @foodheaven last year, and I have been obsessed ever since! (Dare I say it even kicked off my spicy mayo obsession)

I believe you can find their post if you scroll down on their page (go follow!!) but I followed their ingredient list used flour tortillas and sautéed some garlic and cabbage. I cooked the shrimp in some salt, pepper and chipotle seasoning and topped it all off with spicy mayo and green onion! Making spicy Mayo is easy, just mix 1 part mayo with 1 part sriracha (you can adjust the ratio too based on how spicy/creamy you like it)

node.text:
Roasted Broccolini with White Beans, Ricotta, Almonds, and Hot Honey!!!

Recipe went out today to subscribers of good mood food, but if you missed it, it’s also linked in my bio!

This can be eaten hot, cold, as a side, or as an entree — you can even make my vegan almond ricotta and make it plant based. It’s got crunchiness, creaminess, saltiness, sweetness, and spiciness — plus it’s healthy cuz broccolini!!

node.text:
So much happiness the past 2 days and just soaking it all in, reminding myself that this type of full, free, friend-filled weekend wasn’t possible in the same capacity just a year ago, and it feels so sweet to have it back again. 

Pics: Good lighting in my Prius on the way to the marina, an amazing Malibu sunset post-hike with my fiancé, cotton candy nails I painted myself (proud bc longer nails are a luxury for a biter like me), homegrown radishes, visits with my cousin and her new puppy followed by dinner on a boat with my best friend and her family I’ve known for years. Capped it all off with brunch and a beach day with other people I love

I don’t ever want to take any of this for granted

node.text:
Fried Eggs, with Burst Tomatoes, Hemp Seeds, Za’atar, and Fresh Basil! I love making burst tomatoes because they mix into the oil and create this rich, tomatoey flavor

Just add some oil to a pan, add your cherry or grape tomatoes, and cook on medium-low for about 15 minutes until tomatoes quite literally burst
